Document: Polygon2D
Path: godot/classes/class_polygon2d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a Polygon2D node, including appearance, texture mapping, and deformation.

Property: **antialiased** (bool)
Description: If true, polygon edges will be anti-aliased.
Default: false
Method: set_antialiased(value: bool)
Method: get_antialiased()

Property: **color** (Color)
Description: The polygon's fill color. If texture is set, it will be multiplied by this color. It will also be the default color for vertices not set in vertex_colors.
Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1)
Method: set_color(value: Color)
Method: get_color()

Property: **internal_vertex_count** (int)
Description: Number of internal vertices, used for UV mapping.
Default: 0
Method: set_internal_vertex_count(value: int)
Method: get_internal_vertex_count()

Property: **invert_border** (float)
Description: Added padding applied to the bounding box when invert_enabled is set to true. Setting this value too small may result in a "Bad Polygon" error.
Default: 100.0
Method: set_invert_border(value: float)
Method: get_invert_border()

Property: **invert_enabled** (bool)
Description: If true, the polygon will be inverted, containing the area outside the defined points and extending to the invert_border.
Default: false
Method: set_invert_enabled(value: bool)
Method: get_invert_enabled()

Property: **offset** (Vector2)
Description: The offset applied to each vertex.
Default: Vector2(0, 0)
Method: set_offset(value: Vector2)
Method: get_offset()

Property: **polygon** (PackedVector2Array)
Description: The polygon's list of vertices. The final point will be connected to the first.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedVector2Array for more details.
Default: PackedVector2Array()
Method: set_polygon(value: PackedVector2Array)
Method: get_polygon()

Property: **polygons** (Array)
Description: The list of polygons, in case more than one is being represented. Every individual polygon is stored as a PackedInt32Array where each int is an index to a point in polygon. If empty, this property will be ignored, and the resulting single polygon will be composed of all points in polygon, using the order they are stored in.
Default: []
Method: set_polygons(value: Array)
Method: get_polygons()

Property: **skeleton** (NodePath)
Description: Path to a Skeleton2D node used for skeleton-based deformations of this polygon. If empty or invalid, skeletal deformations will not be used.
Default: NodePath("")
Method: set_skeleton(value: NodePath)
Method: get_skeleton()

Property: **texture** (Texture2D)
Description: The polygon's fill texture. Use uv to set texture coordinates.
Method: set_texture(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture()

Property: **texture_offset** (Vector2)
Description: Amount to offset the polygon's texture. If set to Vector2(0, 0), the texture's origin (its top-left corner) will be placed at the polygon's position.
Default: Vector2(0, 0)
Method: set_texture_offset(value: Vector2)
Method: get_texture_offset()

Property: **texture_rotation** (float)
Description: The texture's rotation in radians.
Default: 0.0
Method: set_texture_rotation(value: float)
Method: get_texture_rotation()

Property: **texture_scale** (Vector2)
Description: Amount to multiply the uv coordinates when using texture. Larger values make the texture smaller, and vice versa.
Default: Vector2(1, 1)
Method: set_texture_scale(value: Vector2)
Method: get_texture_scale()

Property: **uv** (PackedVector2Array)
Description: Texture coordinates for each vertex of the polygon. There should be one UV value per polygon vertex. If there are fewer, undefined vertices will use Vector2(0, 0).
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedVector2Array for more details.
Default: PackedVector2Array()
Method: set_uv(value: PackedVector2Array)
Method: get_uv()

Property: **vertex_colors** (PackedColorArray)
Description: Color for each vertex. Colors are interpolated between vertices, resulting in smooth gradients. There should be one per polygon vertex. If there are fewer, undefined vertices will use color.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedColorArray for more details.
Default: PackedColorArray()
Method: set_vertex_colors(value: PackedColorArray)
Method: get_vertex_colors()
---CHUNK---
Document: Polygon2D
Path: godot/classes/class_polygon22d.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing bones and their weights within a Polygon2D node.

Method: add_bone(path: NodePath, weights: PackedFloat32Array) → void
Adds a bone with the specified path and weights.

Method: clear_bones() → void
Removes all bones from this Polygon2D.

Method: erase_bone(index: int) → void
Removes the specified bone from this Polygon2D.

Method: get_bone_count() → int
Returns the number of bones in this Polygon2D.

Method: get_bone_path(index: int) → NodePath
Returns the path to the node associated with the specified bone.

Method: get_bone_weights(index: int) → PackedFloat32Array
Returns the weight values of the specified bone.

Method: set_bone_path(index: int, path: NodePath) → void
Sets the path to the node associated with the specified bone.

Method: set_bone_weights(index: int, weights: PackedFloat32Array) → void
Sets the weight values for the specified bone.